{{Quote|Whenever I do a play there are Star Wars fans at the stage door and they're always lovely &ndash; so excited and so effusive about the storylines and the characters.|Genevieve O'Reilly|<ref name="Express">{{WebCite|url=https://www.express.co.uk/life-style/life/672181/The-Secret-Actress-Genevieve-OReilly-motherhood-parenting-career-family|text=The Secret's Genevieve O'Reilly: My family always comes first|author=Button, Simon|date=2016-05-22|work=[[Wikipedia:Daily Express|''Daily Express'']]|archivedate=20160710071302}}</ref>}}
'''Genevieve O'Reilly''' is an [[Wikipedia:Irish people|Irish]] actress who portrayed [[Mon Mothma]] in [[Star Wars: Episode III Revenge of the Sith|''Star Wars'': Episode III ''Revenge of the Sith'']], and returned to the role for ''[[Rogue One: A Star Wars Story]]'', for five episodes of ''[[Star Wars Rebels]]'', and for two [[Disney+]] television series, ''[[Star Wars: Andor]]'' and ''[[Star Wars: Ahsoka]]''.

==Biography==
===''Star Wars'': Episode III ''Revenge of the Sith''===
On [[June 19]], [[2003]], [[StarWars.com]] announced that O'Reilly was cast into the role of [[Mon Mothma]] in [[Star Wars: Episode III Revenge of the Sith|''Star Wars'': Episode III ''Revenge of the Sith'']], a character previously portrayed by [[Caroline Blakiston]] in [[Star Wars: Episode VI Return of the Jedi|''Star Wars'': Episode VI ''Return of the Jedi'']].<ref name="SW.com">{{SWArchive|url=episode-iii/bts/production/news20030619.html|text=Ep III Cast: The O'Reilly Factor}}</ref> During the original casting process, she was given a scene to audition with, and she tried to not overthink doing a nod to Blakiston.<ref name="Never thought">{{WebCite|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/tv/tv-features/andor-star-genevieve-oreilly-never-thought-shed-get-the-chance-to-flesh-out-mon-mothma-1235221270|text=‘Andor' Star Genevieve O'Reilly Never Thought She'd Get the Chance to Flesh Out Mon Mothma|author=Davids, Brian|date=2022-09-15|work=[[Wikipedia:The Hollywood Reporter|''The Hollywood Reporter'']]|archivedate=20220915165314}}</ref> Cast for her strong resemblance to Blakiston, she carefully studied the British actress' performance in order to capture the character's voice and mannerisms.<ref name="db">{{DB|character|monmothma|Mothma, Mon}}</ref> O'Reilly filmed a few scenes that were meant to set up the formation of the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic|Rebel Alliance]].<ref name="DVD">{{Film|III}} [[Star Wars home video releases#Star_Wars_Episode_III:_Revenge_of_the_Sith|DVD]]</ref> She enjoyed filming those scenes, and saw the costumes as extraordinary. Before the film's release,<ref name="Marriage">{{WebCite|url=https://ew.com/tv/andor-mon-mothma-genevieve-oreilly-episode-4-interview|text=Genevieve O'Reilly reacts to Mon Mothma's crappy marriage on Andor|author=Ross, Dalton|date=2022-09-29|work=[[Entertainment Weekly Books|''Entertainment Weekly'']]|archivedate=20220929171606}}</ref> director<ref name="Revenge">{{Film|III}}</ref> [[George Lucas]] and producer [[Rick McCallum]] wrote to O'Reilly informing her that the scenes of her speaking were [[Content cut from Star Wars|cut]]. The actress respected their decision and reasoned that the film needed to focus on [[Anakin Skywalker|Darth Vader's]] origin. When O'Reilly watched the film, the scenes' exclusion made total sense to her.<ref name="Marriage" />

===''Rogue One: A Star Wars Story''===
{{Quote|Rogue One was a really exciting piece to be a part of. It felt like a genuinely creative project. My memories of it were that it was shot almost like an indie film at times. It was very exciting, and it felt like a hotbed of creativity.|Genevieve O'Reilly|<ref name="ProductionBrief">{{Getty|url=thewaltdisneystudios/allaccess#!asset/gppr5wpqgb4t74974f8s|text=ANDOR Production Brief V3 FINAL 8-04-22|author=[[Gina McIntyre|McIntyre, Gina]]|date=2022-08-04}}</ref>}}
On [[April 7]], [[2016]], it was revealed that O'Reilly would return as Mothma in the [[Star Wars Anthology Series|''Anthology'']] film ''[[Rogue One: A Star Wars Story]]''.<ref name="EW Rogue One">{{WebCite|url=http://ew.com/gallery/rogue-one-star-wars-story/2552023_gallery-rogue-one-star-wars-story/1|text='Rogue One: A Star Wars Story': 20 Clues and Revelations|author=Breznican, Anthony|date=2016-04-07|work=[[Entertainment Weekly Books|''Entertainment Weekly'']]|archivedate=20171224163304}}</ref> She found the film to be a very exciting and creative project.<ref name="ProductionBrief" /> She also voiced her character for several episodes of the TV series ''[[Star Wars Rebels]]'', which aired on [[March 4]], [[2017]].<ref name="CBR">{{WebCite|url=http://www.cbr.com/star-wars-rebels-mon-mothma|text=Mon Mothma Seeks Help In New Star Wars Rebels Clip|author=MacNabb, Matthew|date=2017-03-01|work=[[Wikipedia:Comic Book Resources|''Comic Book Resources'']]|archivedate=20170521054359}}</ref>

===''Andor'' television series===
{{Quote|This is such a gift of a role. It has been a genuine privilege to step into the shoes that Caroline Blakiston originated with George Lucas back in the '80s, as well as revisiting [Mon Mothma] at different times in my life. So to have the opportunity to explore her and delve into her &mdash; not just as a Rebel leader, but also as a woman &mdash; has been something that I didn't expect and something that I'm thrilled to be a part of.|Genevieve O'Reilly on playing Mon Mothma in ''Andor''|<ref name="Never thought" />}}
On [[April 24]], [[2020]], [[StarWars.com]] announced that O'Reilly would reprise her role as Mothma in the upcoming [[Disney+]] show ''[[Star Wars: Andor]]''.<ref name="Cassian" /> The actress was delighted to have the opportunity to better understand her character.<ref name="ProductionBrief" /> She was also excited to explore Mothma as a Rebel leader and as a woman,<ref name="Never thought" /> which included showing the private face of someone who navigates a system of oppression.<ref name="Potent Moment">{{SW|url=news/andor-launch-interview-gilroy-and-cast|text="A Potent Moment in History": Insights from Tony Gilroy and the ''Andor'' Cast}}</ref> O'Reilly wanted to understand the pain and personal cost felt by Caroline Blakiston in ''Return of the Jedi'', and she enjoyed learning more about Mothma's life.<ref name="Never thought" /> She was excited for the audience to see Mothma's journey of becoming the Rebel leader seen in ''Rogue One''.<ref name="Potent Moment" /> O'Reilly liked [[Tony Gilroy]]'s writing because it had several [[Planet|worlds]] and felt universal as well as personal.<ref name="ProductionBrief" /> The actress wanted Mothma's new look in the show to reflect her new stage as a member of high society.<ref name="Marriage" />

O'Reilly felt that the scene with Mothma and [[Luthen Rael]] in the latter's [[Galactic Antiquities and Objects of Interest|gallery]] set up what the crew were trying to do with the character, which was to show her public face and the private woman within it. The set's public space and private interplay behind the corner allowed for creativity between O'Reilly and [[Stellan Skarsgård]], the actor who played Rael. O'Reilly liked working with Skarsgård and thought that he is a brilliant actor.<ref name="Never thought" /> Scenes in the [[Chandrilan Embassy]] were filmed in a practically built set that had a wraparound [[Wikipedia:Light-emitting diode|LED]] screen that used [[Wikipedia:StageCraft|StageCraft]] technology.<ref name="Slashfilm">{{WebCite|url=https://www.slashfilm.com/1090902/heres-where-andor-actually-used-lucasfilms-stagecraft-technology-exclusive|text=Here's Where Andor Actually Used Lucasfilm's StageCraft Technology [Exclusive]|author=Meyer, Joshua|date=2022-11-09|work=[[Wikipedia:/Film|''/Film'']]|archivedate=20221109201335}}</ref> In [[September]], [[2022]], O'Reilly attended the ''Andor'' launch event in [[Wikipedia:Hollywood, Los Angeles|Hollywood]], [[Wikipedia:California|California]].<ref name="Launch event">{{SWYouTube|Fv6hHyIToC0|Diego Luna and the Cast and Crew of Andor &#124; This Week! in Star Wars|sw_url=video/diego-luna-and-the-cast-and-crew-of-andor-this-week-in-star-wars}}</ref>

